<p>The <code>in</code> function tests if a value is in a list of values (returns 1 or empty).</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}$sampleStatus | in('active', 'pending'){close}</pre>
<p>Status '{$sampleStatus}' in list: <b>{$sampleStatus | in('active', 'pending')}</b> (1 = true)</p>

<pre>{open}'red' | in('blue', 'green', 'yellow'){close}</pre>
<p>'red' in colors: <b>{'red' | in('blue', 'green', 'yellow')}</b> (empty = false)</p>

<h2>Conditional Display</h2>
<pre>{open}users{close}
  {open}if $status | in('active', 'pending'){close}
    {open}$name{close}: {open}$status{close}
  {open}/if{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>
<p>Active or pending users:</p>
{users}
  {if $status | in('active', 'pending')}
    {$name}: {$status}<br>
  {/if}
{/users}

<h2>File Type Check</h2>
<pre>{open}$samplePath | afterLast('.') | in('txt', 'pdf', 'doc'){close}</pre>
<p>Is document: <b>{$samplePath | afterLast('.') | in('txt', 'pdf', 'doc')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Example</h2>
<pre>{open}$samplePath | afterLast('.') | lower | in('jpg', 'png', 'gif'){close}</pre>
<p>Is image: <b>{$samplePath | afterLast('.') | lower | in('jpg', 'png', 'gif')}</b></p>
